text: Aydarali () is a rural locality (a selo) and the administrative center of Aydaralinsky Selsoviet, Sterlibashevsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 711 as of 2010. There are 5 streets. == Geography == It is located 19 km from Sterlibashevo. == References == Category:Rural localities in Sterlibashevsky District
title: Aydarali
